com.github.gwtd3.api.core

Class Value

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject
      • com.github.gwtd3.api.core.Value
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Chord.ChordItem

    public class Value
extends com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject
    A Value is an object wrapping a primitive or a complex value.

    A Value is returned from many gwt-d3 functions.

    The wrapped value can be retrieved from the numerous as*() methods.

    Author:
    Anthony Schiochet

      • getProperty

        public final Value getProperty(String propertyName)
        Return the property of this object as a Value.

        This method result is never non-null. The returned value may then be tested for nullity (with isNull()) or for undefinition (with isUndefined()).

        Parameters:
        propertyName - the name of the property to get
        Returns:
        the property value as a value.
